{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"12003b24-f572-4620-a385-fd55996db81f","content":"You already have the HotReload extension referenced. To use it, run your tests with the `--hotreload` flag:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts a watch-style session. When tests fail, you can edit your source/test files and the runner will automatically re-execute affected tests without a full rebuild — giving you a fast red-green feedback loop.\n\n**Key points:**\n- The runner stays active, watching for file changes.\n- Only changed tests (and their dependencies) are re-run.\n- Press `Ctrl+C` to exit the session.\n\nThis is ideal for iterating on fixes: run the command once, then just save your file edits and watch the results update live.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7a632258-80b1-4b51-9457-c5ed781dcc8c","outputTokens":162,"requestId":"9C45:164039:160F042:18CC85F:69F8655E"},"id":"13deb750-ee0d-4f63-81d7-92adfe7e16ec","timestamp":"2026-05-04T09:22:46.119Z","parentId":"eb951128-3126-43aa-9514-573422c8798e"}
